<item>
            <title>[CXF-8682] x-forwarded-proto header causes cxf to not match request to java method</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-8682</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If X-Forwarded-Proto header is set to &quot;HTTP&quot;, then serverside CXF&#160; fails to match &lt;em&gt;Message&lt;/em&gt; to corresponding java method. This happens because of &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cxf/blob/master/rt/frontend/jaxrs/src/main/java/org/apache/cxf/jaxrs/utils/HttpUtils.java#L474&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;HttpUtils#getBaseAddress&lt;/a&gt; being case-sensitive and fails to detect absolute url, that is somehow internally produced by cxf from this x-forwarded-proto and x-forwarded-host headers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#8212;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This uppercase header was produced by NetScaler Load balancer, if this is interesting to you.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
